    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - DISASSEMBLY - INNER AXLE SHAFT REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0201014" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INNER AXLE SHAFT REMOVAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Either remove the outboard section as an assembly as previously described or individual
                components.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_13.xml" xrefid="hl0201003">REMOVAL OF OUTBOARD SECTION OF THE STEERABLE DRIVE
                    END ASSEMBLY
                </hotlnk>
                or refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_10.xml" xrefid="hl0201002">HUB, DRUM AND WHEEL BEARING REMOVAL</hotlnk>,
                <hotlnk document="s02010_11.xml" xrefid="hl0201004">BRAKE AND WHEEL SPINDLE REMOVAL</hotlnk>, and
                <hotlnk document="s02010_12.xml" xrefid="hl0201005">SPINDLE YOKE REMOVAL</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull inner axle shaft from axle housing. If the axle shaft yoke is to be removed, it is
                advisable to loosen the yoke bolt prior to removing the axle shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201026">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0201026" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201026.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Removing Inner Axle Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
